00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:18,559
If it were you, I don't think you'd want irrelevant people

259
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,680
going through your results randomly.

260
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:22,479
I was just stating facts.

261
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:24,100
She wasn't good at math to begin with.

262
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:26,980
She didn't even make it to our grade's top 100 in the last midterm exam.

263
00:17:26,980 --> 00:17:30,319
If we exclude her Integrated Science results, she'd be in the top 20.

264
00:17:30,319 --> 00:17:34,200
Even if we include those results, I could also be in the top 20.

265
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:39,500
Why can't I talk about her bad results?

266
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:42,560
She even made so many mistakes in her regular homework.

267
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:44,980
What is this?

268
00:17:47,260 --> 00:17:49,399
"The first time I saw you,

269
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,559
you were sitting on the grass and playing guitar.

270
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:55,040
There were so many people around, but I saw you right away."

271
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:58,680
Su Zaizai was writing a love letter to someone!

272
00:17:58,680 --> 00:17:59,919
Do you know this guitar player?

273
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:02,100
This is someone else's privacy.

274
00:18:04,660 --> 00:18:07,800
You only said that because it was Su Zaizai's, right?

275
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:12,440
You can go back if you don't want to help.

276
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:19,825
   

277
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,700
Rang Rang.

278
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:33,140
You're here as well?

279
00:18:43,540 --> 00:18:45,220
The first one over here.

280
00:18:50,060 --> 00:18:51,360
Rang Rang,

281
00:18:52,140 --> 00:18:55,720
did you see something?

282
00:19:00,040 --> 00:19:01,340
No.

283
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:04,540
Your name is written so big

284
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:07,520
that it's unforgettable.

285
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:28,919
They're planning to switch to a new student society

286
00:19:28,919 --> 00:19:30,359
even before Senior Qianyu leaves.

287
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:31,540
What do you mean?

288
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:34,700
Isn't that guy from the Guitar Society?

289
00:19:34,700 --> 00:19:36,660
Is that so?

290
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:40,020
 Su Zaizai was writing a love letter to someone! 

291
00:19:40,020 --> 00:19:41,880
 Do you know this guitar player? 

292
00:19:45,820 --> 00:19:47,119
Thank you.

293
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:48,039
You're welcome.

294
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:49,759
You can just ask me directly if there's anything else

295
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:51,240
you don't know about guitars.

296
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:55,759
It's a good thing we asked him.

297
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:59,340
Otherwise, it'd be so embarrassing if Senior Qianyu saw the ridiculous music theories

298
00:19:59,340 --> 00:20:01,200
I wrote in the letter.

299
00:20:03,180 --> 00:20:04,320
Zhang Lurang!

300
00:20:04,780 --> 00:20:05,960
Hey,

301
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:08,540
are Guan Fang and I invisible?

302
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:11,079
You have a better understanding of yourself now.

303
00:20:11,080 --> 00:20:13,759
What were you two talking about over here?

304
00:20:13,760 --> 00:20:15,300
You looked so excited.

305
00:20:16,260 --> 00:20:18,060
It's a secret.

306
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:25,380
By the way, we'll have a fitness test in this class

307
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:27,380
and you boys will be doing pull-ups.

308
00:20:27,380 --> 00:20:29,180
How many can you do, Rang Rang?

309
00:20:29,180 --> 00:20:30,580
It's a secret.

310
00:20:37,860 --> 00:20:39,740
Are you two the only ones left?

311
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:43,940
It's your turn. I'll hold your ankles.

312
00:20:43,940 --> 00:20:45,800
Come on, get ready.

313
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:48,600
Sir.

314
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:51,679
Mr. Xu asked me to get the key to the basketball equipment room.

315
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:53,880
Has Class 1 finished the fitness test?

316
00:20:55,260 --> 00:20:56,460
I think...

317
00:20:57,120 --> 00:20:58,940
I left the key in the office.

318
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:00,999
I'll go and get it.

319
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:01,879
Sure.

320
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:04,079
You guys can record your own scores.

321
00:21:04,080 --> 00:21:05,780
Okay!

322
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:12,039
I think you're more reliable.

323
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,759
You don't look like someone who'd cheat.

324
00:21:13,760 --> 00:21:15,060
Record their scores for me.

325
00:21:15,060 --> 00:21:16,760
Got it.

326
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:21,800
Ready.

327
00:21:24,940 --> 00:21:26,340
Start.

328
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:53,020
30 seconds to go.

329
00:21:55,980 --> 00:21:56,700
22.

330
00:21:56,700 --> 00:21:57,900
21.

331
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:01,319
It was 22.

332
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,540
Those that don't meet the standards don't count.

333
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,260
Time's up.

334
00:22:26,260 --> 00:22:28,120
Hey, you guys did 36, right?

335
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:31,080
30.

336
00:22:32,020 --> 00:22:33,300
Yours was 26.

337
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:35,660
You just passed the test.

338
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:42,380
Rang Rang, you're truly stern and impartial.

339
00:22:52,860 --> 00:22:57,020
Rang Rang, are you having a bad day?

340
00:23:02,820 --> 00:23:03,920
No.

341
00:23:04,480 --> 00:23:06,119
You're still denying it.

342
00:23:06,120 --> 00:23:08,320
You were already touching your neck.

343
00:23:11,860 --> 00:23:13,060
 Rang Rang, 

344
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:17,320
 did you see something? 

345
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:19,740
 No. 

346
00:23:21,120 --> 00:23:22,980
 Your name is written so big 

347
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:25,920
 that it's unforgettable. 

348
00:23:27,120 --> 00:23:30,500
 You didn't see what I put in my homework, did you? 

349
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:33,799
♫  I guess I’ve fallen in love with you  ♫

350
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:36,940
Could it be that you got jealous because you thought

351
00:23:36,940 --> 00:23:39,499
I wrote that for someone else?

352
00:23:39,500 --> 00:23:41,420
♫  It’s unexplainable  ♫

353
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:42,480
No.

354
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:46,159
Ahem, I have to lecture you about this.

355
00:23:46,160 --> 00:23:47,959
You couldn't even recognize my handwriting

356
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:50,480
after all the tutoring classes we've had.

357
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,760
This is so heartbreaking.

358
00:23:53,740 --> 00:23:58,359
As a punishment, you should read my notes carefully again.

359
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:00,080
You'll have to remember it this time.

360
00:24:00,940 --> 00:24:06,260
As for making me suffer in the PE class, I'll forgive you.

361
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:13,099
♫  I'm not afraid of having regrets as long as you’re with me  ♫

362
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:18,319
♫  Even if it makes it hard for me to let go  ♫

363
00:24:18,320 --> 00:24:19,720
A'Rang,

364
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:22,039
I warmed up some milk just now, so I got you a glass as well.

365
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:23,119
Thanks, Uncle.

366
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:28,059
♫  But now, I don’t want to hesitate anymore  ♫

367
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:30,959
What happened? Why are you so happy?

368
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:33,240
♫  I believe you'll walk to me step by step  ♫

369
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:34,640
I...

370
00:24:34,641 --> 00:24:37,160
♫  I believe you will come to know the true me  ♫

371
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:40,225
♫  Just like the moon and the sunset  ♫

372
00:24:40,225 --> 00:24:41,624
   

373
00:24:41,625 --> 00:24:43,679
♫  They come in turn but never miss each other  ♫

374
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:45,460
All right then, go to bed early.

375
00:24:45,460 --> 00:24:46,999
Remember to drink your milk.

376
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,339
Okay.

377
00:24:48,340 --> 00:24:52,000
♫  I believe I'll pass by unintentionally  ♫

378
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:55,699
♫  For love, we should be brave  ♫

379
00:24:55,700 --> 00:25:01,399
♫  Thank you for getting into my heart  ♫

380
00:25:03,580 --> 00:25:06,699
Brother Qianyu, what brings you to the Grade 10 area?

381
00:25:06,699 --> 00:25:08,800
I'm heading to the Office of Academic Affairs for a stamp.

382
00:25:10,360 --> 00:25:12,900
Are you leaving very soon?

383
00:25:12,900 --> 00:25:13,719
Yes.

384
00:25:13,719 --> 00:25:16,059
Two more weeks to go, I think.

385
00:25:16,059 --> 00:25:18,340
That's so soon.

386
00:25:19,020 --> 00:25:22,100
Oh! I have one more recital before I go abroad.

387
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:24,840
If you have time, you can come and watch it.

388
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:26,574
Consider it a farewell.

389
00:25:26,575 --> 00:25:29,575
   

390
00:25:45,825 --> 00:25:48,100
   

391
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:53,679
Hang on, Brother Qianyu only gave me this one ticket.

392
00:25:53,680 --> 00:25:58,360
Does this mean I'm that special one?

393
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:10,879
Two days ago, you were so upset about Senior Qianyu leaving this country.

394
00:26:10,879 --> 00:26:13,420
Why are you in such a good mood today?

395
00:26:17,140 --> 00:26:18,299
You're over the moon.

396
00:26:18,299 --> 00:26:19,960
Did you win the lottery?

397
00:26:19,960 --> 00:26:23,141
You can say that. It's a good thing anyway.

398
00:26:24,120 --> 00:26:26,060
Why do you all have good things going on recently?

399
00:26:26,060 --> 00:26:28,940
A'Rang is also in a good mood today for some reason.

400
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:33,320
So, what's up? You haven't told us yet.

401
00:26:35,820 --> 00:26:38,960
Don't envy me after I tell you guys about it.

402
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:45,080
Senior Qianyu invited me to his recital next Friday night.

403
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:47,120
So?

404
00:26:48,660 --> 00:26:51,519
So, I won't be joining you guys that day.

405
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:52,919
I'm letting you know in advance.

406
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:54,879
Why wouldn't you join us?

407
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:55,959
We're going as well.

408
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:57,200
What?

409
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:59,399
We bumped into Senior Qianyu at the basketball court during lunch break.

410
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:00,679
He told us about it.

411
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:02,420
He even asked all of us to attend it.

412
00:27:03,120 --> 00:27:05,960
So, I wasn't the only one.

413
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:09,620
What's wrong with her again?

414
00:27:10,980 --> 00:27:14,200
The special treatment she thought she had is gone.

415
00:27:20,260 --> 00:27:22,219
♫  In the vast sky of a clear day, a white cloud is drifting by  ♫

416
00:27:22,219 --> 00:27:24,099
♫  In the vast sky of a clear day, a white cloud is drifting by  ♫

417
00:27:24,099 --> 00:27:28,240
♫  It catches my eyes, and it's as pure as you  ♫

418
00:27:28,240 --> 00:27:30,299
♫  Azure blue is like a dream  ♫

419
00:27:30,299 --> 00:27:32,099
♫  Transforming into a drifting bottle  ♫

420
00:27:32,099 --> 00:27:36,300
♫  Guiding me slowly closer to your heart  ♫

421
00:27:36,300 --> 00:27:40,140
♫  The wind's voice of longing must resonate with the clouds  ♫

422
00:27:40,140 --> 00:27:44,220
♫  Condensing above us into rain that falls  ♫

423
00:27:44,220 --> 00:27:46,260
♫  Somewhere within the crevice of the Earth  ♫

424
00:27:46,260 --> 00:27:48,040
♫  There's a parallel universe  ♫

425
00:27:48,040 --> 00:27:52,399
♫  There lies our best time  ♫

426
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:56,039
Why do you have to take extra lessons with Zhang Lurang on weekends?

427
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:57,819
 The monthly exam coming up soon. 

428
00:27:57,819 --> 00:28:01,200
 You know I messed up in my previous math exam. 

429
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:03,439
Who can do the shoe shopping with me then?

430
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:05,640
He Yu and Fu Yao are both busy.

431
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:07,560
 How about Guan Fang? 

432
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:10,500
 Boys might provide a different insight. 

433
00:28:12,220 --> 00:28:13,820
You've got a point.

434
00:28:13,820 --> 00:28:16,080
I'll ask him then.

435
00:28:19,780 --> 00:28:22,280
Hello, Guan Fang? Are you free tomorrow?

436
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:24,880
Go shopping with your grandma?

437
00:28:25,420 --> 00:28:28,700
Oh, forget it then. Bye-bye.

438
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:36,780
Who else can I ask?

439
00:28:42,420 --> 00:28:45,179
Do you have other business?

440
00:28:45,179 --> 00:28:47,860
You're all dressed up as if you're meeting someone important.

441
00:28:47,860 --> 00:28:48,860
What?

442
00:28:48,860 --> 00:28:50,319
That's nonsense!

443
00:28:50,320 --> 00:28:53,860
Don't put it like that. I usually dress this way.

444
00:28:53,860 --> 00:28:55,860
Don't flatter yourself.

445
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:58,559
I didn't say it was me.

446
00:28:58,560 --> 00:29:01,061
Let's move. It's getting late.

447
00:29:01,099 --> 00:29:04,460
How could you not appreciate what you've been granted?

448
00:29:04,460 --> 00:29:06,919
I freed up my busy schedule to come shopping with you,

449
00:29:06,919 --> 00:29:09,420
but you're not showing any gratitude.

450
00:29:10,980 --> 00:29:13,999
But then again, am I the only one here today?

451
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:16,060
Yes, it's just you.

452
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:18,800
You've got a good taste

453
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:21,119
for choosing me.

454
00:29:21,120 --> 00:29:22,759
This had nothing to do with my taste.

455
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:25,600
I asked everyone else and you are the only one available.

456
00:29:25,620 --> 00:29:26,900
Oh, hold on.

457
00:29:26,900 --> 00:29:28,519
The senior gentleman was free as well,

458
00:29:28,520 --> 00:29:30,759
but I was worried about a generation gap in aesthetics.

459
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:32,639
So on second thought, I asked you.

460
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:34,839
At least, you're a boy.

461
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:37,300
Your aesthetics should be somewhat different from a girl's.

462
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:39,880
What did you mean by "at least"?

463
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:50,560
Wow! How pretty!

464
00:29:57,500 --> 00:29:58,580
Didn't you say that they're pretty?

465
00:29:58,580 --> 00:29:59,720
Try them on.

466
00:30:00,280 --> 00:30:01,200
Forget it.

467
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:02,900
I'm not here to buy these today.

468
00:30:03,600 --> 00:30:04,820
Huh?

469
00:30:11,040 --> 00:30:13,400
Hi, excuse me. I'd like to try these on.

470
00:30:19,780 --> 00:30:21,320
That was close.

471
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:24,900
Why did you buy high heels when you've never worn them before?

472
00:30:24,900 --> 00:30:26,159
I'm a size 37.

473
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:28,500
These shoes are also a size 37. Hence, they should fit me.

474
00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:29,779
Besides,

475
00:30:29,779 --> 00:30:32,940
I'm walking much more steadily than I did just now, okay?

476
00:30:49,660 --> 00:30:52,520
But didn't you like that pair of sneakers very much?

477
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:57,119
It's about choices.

478
00:30:57,120 --> 00:30:58,520
We can't have it all.

479
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:06,400
You're doing this for Senior Qianyu's recital, right?

480
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:08,640
Why are you asking when you already know it?

481
00:31:10,280 --> 00:31:13,340
If you were Senior Qianyu, what would you think of me?

482
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:16,280
How would I know?

483
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:19,560
Yeah, well, it's not like you'll ever be him.

484
00:31:23,281 --> 00:31:26,660
However, I'd like to thank you for shopping with me for so long today.

485
00:31:26,660 --> 00:31:28,879
It's been a long time since anyone has been so patient with me.

486
00:31:28,880 --> 00:31:30,360
I'm very happy.

487
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:43,740
Here, let me.

488
00:31:44,420 --> 00:31:45,020
Thanks.

489
00:31:45,090 --> 00:31:48,700
♫  I admitted that I’d made a mistake  ♫

490
00:31:48,700 --> 00:31:52,400
 The youthful thoughts that year seemed to have exposed their traces 

491
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:55,060
 along with the early summer. 

492
00:31:55,060 --> 00:31:56,660
Sorry, please excuse me.

493
00:31:57,500 --> 00:32:00,039
 Thus, they put on a not-so-clever disguise. 

494
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:03,360
 He held up a safe area with his arms 

495
00:32:04,340 --> 00:32:06,980
 but blamed the heat for his sweaty palms. 

496
00:32:06,980 --> 00:32:09,880
♫  But give me some time so I could fix it  ♫

497
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:12,220
 And only one of the two parties knew 

498
00:32:12,220 --> 00:32:15,680
 that the seemingly coincidental encounter was actually a calculation 

499
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:17,020
 more sophisticated than a math question. 

500
00:32:17,020 --> 00:32:19,720
♫  my mind’s been overwhelmed  ♫

501
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:22,400
 The gifts they mustered the courage to give 

502
00:32:22,400 --> 00:32:24,580
 were cloaked in mischief. 

503
00:32:25,580 --> 00:32:31,040
 They chose to silently say the words "I want you to be happy" in their hearts. 

504
00:32:32,290 --> 00:32:34,240
♫  I wanna love you more just like before  ♫

505
00:32:34,240 --> 00:32:36,240
 However, love would always quietly slip out 

506
00:32:36,280 --> 00:32:37,640
♫  I miss getting up with you  ♫

507
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:40,260
 through every glance at him. 

508
00:32:40,260 --> 00:32:43,700
 It was all in a diary secretly written under the desk lamp. 

509
00:32:43,700 --> 00:32:47,160
 These trivial and scrupulous moments 

510
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:50,260
 are like the candy a child hides in their pocket. 

511
00:32:50,260 --> 00:32:53,220
 If we unwrap the candy and sniff it during the night, 

512
00:32:53,220 --> 00:32:56,940
 tomorrow would seem a bit more worthy of anticipation. 

513
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:03,900
 Let's all relax after such a long class. 

514
00:33:03,900 --> 00:33:05,980
 Let's play a game of imitation. 

515
00:33:05,980 --> 00:33:08,799
 We shall start with Guan Fang. 

516
00:33:08,800 --> 00:33:10,260
 Each of you will imitate an animal. 

517
00:33:10,260 --> 00:33:11,600
 Here we go. 

518
00:33:44,620 --> 00:33:46,120
 Hurry up! 

519
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:48,860
 Meow. 

